cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the task of detecting human-object interactions in images, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a novel attention-based network that learns to highlight regions in an image based on the appearance of each instance, which involves machine learning techniques. Hence, it is also likely to belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The proposed network is designed to recognize HOIs, which is a task related to robotics and automation. Therefore, it could also be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
